<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,433,742]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
As evidenced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bauret L. &amp; Grall A. &amp; Senterre B. &amp; Rouhan G. &amp; Hennequin S. &amp; Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y." box="[394,628,433,460]" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 14" part="202" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.202.1.1" refString="Bauret L., Grall A., Senterre B., Rouhan G., Hennequin S., Ebihara A. &amp; Dubuisson J. - Y. 2015. New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean. Phytotaxa 202: 1 - 14. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 202.1.1" title="New circumscription of Trichomanes cupressoides Desvaux (Hymenophyllaceae), an endemic filmy fern from Seychelles (Indian Ocean), and new insights into the genus Abrodictyum C. Presl in the western Indian Ocean" type="journal article" year="2015">
Bauret 
<emphasis box="[480,539,433,459]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
, several paleotropical species formerly attributed to 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1399,433,459]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1247,1399,433,459]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Trichomanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the genus is mostly neotropical) are morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Presl (Presl" authorityYear="1843" box="[942,1092,469,495]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1092,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Abrodictyum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. However, the single Comorian species 
<taxonomicName authority="Bosch" authorityName="Bosch" box="[411,615,504,530]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boivinii">
<emphasis box="[411,532,504,530]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">T. boivinii</emphasis>
Bosch
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[907,1243,504,530]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudorigidum">
<emphasis box="[907,1243,504,530]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Abrodictyum pseudorigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in the archipelago (see 
<figureCitation box="[432,504,539,565]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1000,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[189,1399,1000,1847]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Terrestrial Comorian Hymenophyllaceae. A. Abrodictyum pseudorigidum Bauret &amp; Dubuisson, first identified as A. rigidum (Sw.) Ebihara &amp; Dubuisson, (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6771, P 00312031). B. Trichomanes boivinii Bosch, new for the archipelago according to the last inventories (as discussed in text) (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6675, P 00311390). Scale bar for both species = 3 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/896411/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). The rhizomes of 
<taxonomicName box="[726,845,539,565]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boivinii">
<emphasis box="[726,845,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">T. boivinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are short-creeping while those of 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudorigidum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Abrodictyum pseudorigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are mostly suberect to erect. The main differences concern the ultimate segment shape. In 
<taxonomicName box="[305,425,609,635]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boivinii">
<emphasis box="[305,425,609,635]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">T. boivinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ultimate segments are multi-veined, ovate, spatulate and more or less toothed. In 
<taxonomicName box="[189,526,645,671]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Abrodictyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudorigidum">
<emphasis box="[189,526,645,671]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Abrodictyum pseudorigidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ultimate segments are uni-veined, linear, and entire with tapered ends. Compared to 
<bibRefCitation author="Tardieu-Blot M. - L." box="[349,584,680,707]" editor="Humbert H." journalOrPublisher="famille" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="16 - 38" part="3" refString="Tardieu-Blot M. - L. 1951. Hymenophyllacees. In: Humbert H. (ed.) Flore de Madagascar et des Comores, famille 3: 16 - 38. MNHN, Paris." title="Hymenophyllacees" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Flore de Madagascar et des Comores" year="1951">Tardieu-Blot (1951)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Roux J. P." box="[641,793,680,706]" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" part="23" refString="Roux J. P. 2009. Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands. Strelitzia 23." title="Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands" type="journal volume" year="2009">Roux (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[806,925,680,706]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boivinii">
<emphasis box="[806,925,680,706]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">T. boivinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is new for the archipelago, although the species had already been reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhn F. A. M." box="[629,783,715,742]" journalOrPublisher="Engelman, Leipzig" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refString="Kuhn F. A. M. 1868. Filices Africanae. Engelman, Leipzig." title="Filices Africanae" type="book" year="1868">Kuhn (1868)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
